result.execSummary:
The defendant Tramaine D Green #00471484 was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Firearm-Convicted of a Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

9:34 AM Cases called: 22CF183, 22TR2134, and 22TR2274. Prosecuting attorney Brenda L. Yaskal in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Tramaine D Green #00471484 appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Michael Yang in court for Tramaine D Green #00471484. Defendant is currently at Dodge Correctional. Waived his right to be personally present. Agreement recited by State. Court reviewed the rights & elements. Defendant pled guilty to count 1 of 22CF183. Court found defendant guilty, entered judgment. Counts 2 & 3 dismissed and read in. 22TR2134 and 22TR2274 dismissed. Sentencing statements. Court sentenced the defendant to serve 4 years in prison, consecutive to any other sentence currently serving; 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision. $518.00 costs. Conditions of extended supervision include: Maintain absolute sobriety. Complete an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment recommendations. Submit DNA sample. Defendant is eligible for the challenge incarceration program and the substance abuse program. 1 day credit. 9:45 AM
